In those halcyon days prior to the advent of the internet, the absence from a photographic engagement precluded any possibility of rectification by the publication. Consequently, when the periodical was released, it was bereft of authentic imagery, supplanted instead by rudimentary representations, not even rising to the level of illustrations, but rather mere caricatures. For instance, Raekwon the Chef was portrayed with a chef's hat, and Ol' Dirty Bastard was depicted in the company of an inflatable effigy. I was of the opinion that these illustrations did not adequately convey the gravity of the musical virtuosity I had observed. The portrayal struck me as lacking in sophistication.
